cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SC, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with data structures for proximity queries and Voronoi diagrams, which are fundamental topics in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The paper also presents data structures with space and query time trade-offs, which are typical of data structure research, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The paper also deals with Voronoi diagrams, which are a topic in both computational geometry and graph theory, suggesting cs.GR (Graph Theory) as a possible category. The paper also presents a new representation for Voronoi diagrams that can be incrementally updated, which is a topic in control theory and robotics, suggesting cs.SC (Systems and Control) and cs.SY (Robotics) as possible categories.
